wsTrapMIB.contactinfo: Symbol Technologies, Inc. Customer Service Postal: One Symbol Plaza Holtsville, NY 11742-1300 USA Tel: +1. 631.738.6213 E-mail: support@symbol.com Web: http://www.symbol.com/support
wsTrapMIB.description: This MIB defines all the Traps that can occur within the WLAN module. The following functionality is provided for Enabling/Disabling traps : 1. Each trap has a 'read-write' Enable 'Truth-Value' Flag associated with it. 2. The Traps are organized in groups on a per module basis. Each module has two 'doActionNow' variables to Enable & Disable ALL the traps within that module. Setting these variables directly changes the Enable Flags of all the traps within that module. 3. There is a Global Trap Enable 'Truth-Value' Flag which determines whether any trap is sent out or not. Setting this variable does not affect the settings of the individual traps.

wsTrapWirelessStationAssociated.name: wsTrapWirelessStationAssociated
wsTrapWirelessStationAssociated.description: A station has associated to the wlan controller. Solution: If this is not an authorized station, add it to the Access Control List or increase your wireless security. Other Possibilities: None. Severity: TP_SEV_NORM Message: Station: [mac], radio: [uint]

wsTrapWirelessStationDisassociated.name: wsTrapWirelessStationDisassociated
wsTrapWirelessStationDisassociated.description: A station has disassociated from the wlan controller. Solution: Make sure your station is powered on and within the service area of the wlan controller. Other Possibilities: The station may not have the correct credentials to associate to the wlan. Severity: TP_SEV_NORM Message: Station: [mac], radio: [uint]

wsTrapWirelessStationDeniedAssociationOn.name: wsTrapWirelessStationDeniedAssociationOnCapability
wsTrapWirelessStationDeniedAssociationOn.description: The station was denied association due to conflicts in the 802.11 capabilities field. Solution: The station needs to be updated to support the correct capability fields. Other Possibilities: None. Message: Station: [mac], radio: [uint]

wsTrapWirelessStationDeniedAssociationOn.name: wsTrapWirelessStationDeniedAssociationOnShortPreamble
wsTrapWirelessStationDeniedAssociationOn.description: The station was denied association because it does not support short preamble. Solution: Turn off short preamble on the wlan or update the station so it can support short preamble. Other Possibilities: None. Message: Station: [mac], radio: [uint]

wsTrapWirelessStationDeniedAssociationOn.name: wsTrapWirelessStationDeniedAssociationOnSpectrum
wsTrapWirelessStationDeniedAssociationOn.description: The station was denied association because it does not support spectrum magagement. Solution: The country and channel of operation require spectrum management on stations. Update your station or try a different channel. Other Possibilities: None. Message: Station: [mac], radio: [uint]

wsTrapWirelessStationDeniedAssociationOn.name: wsTrapWirelessStationDeniedAssociationOnErr
wsTrapWirelessStationDeniedAssociationOn.description: The station was denied association because the 802.11 packet was malformed. Solution: Check your station hardware and software for errors. Other Possibilities: Interference or a cracking attempt. Severity: TP_SEV_WARN Message: Station: [mac], radio: [uint]

wsTrapWirelessStationDeniedAssociationOn.name: wsTrapWirelessStationDeniedAssociationOnSSID
wsTrapWirelessStationDeniedAssociationOn.description: The station was denied association because the SSID supplied by the MU was too large. Solution: Check your MU software. It appears to be sending a malformed association request. Other Possibilities: Interference or a cracking attempt. Severity: TP_SEV_WARN Message: Station: [mac], radio: [uint]

wsTrapWirelessStationDeniedAssociationOn.name: wsTrapWirelessStationDeniedAssociationOnRates
wsTrapWirelessStationDeniedAssociationOn.description: The station was denied association because it does not support the rates required. Solution: Reduce the supported rate set on the radio or update the radio on the station to support the required rates. Other Possibilities: None. Message: Station: [mac], radio: [uint]

wsTrapWirelessStationDeniedAssociationOn.name: wsTrapWirelessStationDeniedAssociationOnInvalidWPA
wsTrapWirelessStationDeniedAssociationOn.description: The station was denied association because it did not send a WPA/WPA2 element. Solution: Ensure the station supports WPA/WPA2 or turn off WPA/WPA2. Other Possibilities: None. Message: Station: [mac], radio: [uint]

wsTrapWirelessStationDeniedAssociationAs.name: wsTrapWirelessStationDeniedAssociationAsPortCapacityReached
wsTrapWirelessStationDeniedAssociationAs.description: The station was denied association because the radio it was attempting to associate to has reached its station limit. Solution: Increase the number of stations that can associate to the radio or increase radio density to allow for more stations. Other Possibilities: None. Message: Station: [mac], radio: [uint], maximum Station: [uint]

wsTrapWirelessStationTkipCounterMeasures.name: wsTrapWirelessStationTkipCounterMeasures
wsTrapWirelessStationTkipCounterMeasures.description: There have been 2 or more TKIP MIC checksum failures in the last 60 seconds, as a result that Wireless Lan has been disabled for 60 seconds. MIC failures can occur either because someone is trying to attack the network and guess your TKIP keys, or because of some stations that have drivers that generate invalid frames. Solution: View the system logs to see which wireless station is generating these MIC failures. If it is on your network, then take that station off the network for now. Contact support. Other Possibilities: If your network is setup for eap authentication with TKIP encryption, and there are frequent reauthentications, MIC failures can occur. If this is the case, try reducing the frequency of re-authentications, and see if it helps with the countermeasures. Again see if the failures are caused by one particular station. Severity: TP_SEV_WARN Message: Activated

wsTrapWirelessStationDeniedAuthenticatio.name: wsTrapWirelessStationDeniedAuthentication
wsTrapWirelessStationDeniedAuthenticatio.description: The station was denied authentication due to the maximum number of stations being reached for the controller. Solution: Add another controller to you network or reduce the number of stations. Other Possibilities: The authentication algorithm being used by the WLAN is not supported by the station or a malformed auth packet from the station. Severity: TP_SEV_MAJOR Message: Station: [mac]

wsTrapWirelessStationRadiusAuthFailed.name: wsTrapWirelessStationRadiusAuthFailed
wsTrapWirelessStationRadiusAuthFailed.description: The station was denied access to the wlan because Radius authentication failed. Solution: Check radius server connectivity and the stations username/password. Other Possibilities: None Severity: TP_SEV_MAJOR Message: Station: [mac], radio: [uint]

wsTrapWirelessStationVlanChanged.name: wsTrapWirelessStationVlanChanged
wsTrapWirelessStationVlanChanged.description: Station's vlan id is changed. Solution: Check IP connectivity with Peer IP-address. Other Possibilities: None. Message: Station: [mac], assigned with new vlan id:[uint] on wlan :[uint]

wsTrapEnableWirelessStationVlanChanged.name: wsTrapEnableWirelessStationVlanChanged
wsTrapEnableWirelessStationVlanChanged.description: Enable the trap for station VLAN change

wsTrapSmtpNotifyWirelessStationTrap.description: Enable or disable e-mail notification of Wireless Station traps. Please see the definition of SmtpNotifyBitMap for the usage of this field.

wsTrapWirelessRadioAdopted.name: wsTrapWirelessRadioAdopted
wsTrapWirelessRadioAdopted.description: A radio was adopted by the wlan controller. Solution: If this is not a authorized station, turn off adopt-unconf-radio Other Possibilities: None. Severity: TP_SEV_NORM Message: Radio [str], on Radio-Port [mac] at AP IP Address [ip]

wsTrapWirelessRadioUnadopted.name: wsTrapWirelessRadioUnadopted
wsTrapWirelessRadioUnadopted.description: A radio was un-adopted from the wlan controller. Solution: Check network connectivity between the controller and radio port. Other Possibilities: The radio was removed or reconfigured. Message: Radio [str] on Radio-Port [mac] at AP IP Address [ip]

wsTrapWirelessRadioDetectedRadar.name: wsTrapWirelessRadioDetectedRadar
wsTrapWirelessRadioDetectedRadar.description: A radio detected radar on its channel of operation and is switching channels. Solution: Retry the channel later. Other Possibilities: Interference. Severity: TP_SEV_WARN Message: Radio [str] on Radio-Port [mac], channel [uint]

wsTrapSmtpNotifyWirelessRadioTrap.name: wsTrapSmtpNotifyWirelessRadioTrap

wsTrapWirelessUnapprovedAPRemoved.name: wsTrapWirelessUnapprovedAPRemoved

wsTrapEnableWirelessUnapprovedAPRemoved.name: wsTrapEnableWirelessUnapprovedAPRemoved

wsTrapWirelessSelfHealActivate.name: wsTrapWirelessSelfHealActivate
wsTrapWirelessSelfHealActivate.description: This radio is attempting to cover for a neighboring AP that is down. Solution: 1. Verify that the neighboring AP is still adopted. 2. Verify that there are no physical obstructions between the down AP and other APs. Other Possibilities: 1. The neighboring AP may have a physical obstruction or has become unadopted. 2. Mis-configuration. Set the healing AP and the down AP to not be neighbors. Message: Activated

wsTrapSmtpNotifyWirelessSelfHealTrap.name: wsTrapSmtpNotifyWirelessSelfHealTrap
wsTrapSmtpNotifyWirelessSelfHealTrap.description: Enable or disable e-mail notification of Wireless Self Healing traps. Please see the definition of SmtpNotifyBitMap for the usage of this field.

wsTrapWirelessIdsMuEvent.name: wsTrapWirelessIdsMuEvent

Solution: This may be indicative of an attack on your wireless LAN. If the MU is one of your own, it may be experiencing problems. Other Possibilities: The threshold may be set too low, make it higher. Severity: TP_SEV_WARN

wsTrapWirelessIdsRadioEvent.name: wsTrapWirelessIdsRadioEvent

The radio is being filtered for the configured number of seconds. Solution: This may be indicative of an attack on your wireless LAN. If the radio is one of your own, it may be experiencing problems. Other Possibilities: The threshold may be set too low, make it higher. Severity: TP_SEV_WARN

wsTrapWirelessIdsSwitchEvent.name: wsTrapWirelessIdsSwitchEvent

The switch is being filtered for the configured number of seconds. Solution: This may be indicative of an attack on your wireless LAN. If the switch is one of your own, it may be experiencing problems. Other Possibilities: The threshold may be set too low, make it higher. Severity: TP_SEV_WARN

wsTrapWirelessStatStation.description: This trap is generated when the user set values are violated for the station. Solution: Check the stations for proper operation. Other Possibilities: None. Severity: TP_SEV_WARN Message: Threshold [str], value [str] [str], Station [mac], Station [ip]

wsTrapWirelessStatModule.name: wsTrapWirelessStatModule
wsTrapWirelessStatModule.description: This trap is generated when the user set values are violated for the wlan-module. Solution: Check the wlan-module for proper operation. Other Possibilities: None. Severity: TP_SEV_WARN Message: Threshold [str], value [str] [str]

wsTrapWirelessWlanVlanUserLimitReached.name: wsTrapWirelessWlanVlanUserLimitReached

Future association will not be assigned to this VLAN. Solution: Increase the limit on the number of users for that VLAN/WLAN. Other Possibilities: Assign more VLANs to that WLAN. Message: wlan [uint], vlan [uint] reached user limit [uint]

Solution: Configure the route on this device and route configuration on intermediate routers so that web-portal is reachable from this device. Check to make sure the web-portal server is powered on. Other Possibilities: None. Severity: TP_SEV_MAJOR Message: WLAN index [int], Hotspot page URL [str]
